#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIR.rst:60
#: 4b5732b394c34464a9322cd8b95fcd0d
msgid ""
"Node transitions follow three rules: 1) if a :math:`S` state node has "
":math:`I` state neighbors, each :math:`I` state neighbor exposes the "
":math:`S` state node with probability :math:`\\beta` (S→E); 2) the "
":math:`E` state node becomes :math:`I` with probability :math:`\\alpha` "
"(E→I); 3) the :math:`I` state node is recovered to the :math:`R` state "
"with probability :math:`\\gamma` (I→R)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIR.rst:66
#: 43a6e41161d64622b778e4d324c49227
msgid "SEIR model diagram"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIR.rst:71
#: 0bb430658a584802a904219b2aa97a90
msgid ""
"Node states are represented by three Boolean indicator vectors :math:`h, "
"e, r \\in \\{0,1\\}^N`, where :math:`h_i=1` denotes ``infected`` or "
"``exposed``, :math:`h_i=0` denotes ``recovered`` or ``susceptible``, and "
":math:`(h_i,e_i,r_i)=(1,0,0)` denotes ``infected``, "
":math:`(h_i,e_i,r_i)=(1,1,0)` denotes ``exposed``, "
":math:`(h_i,e_i,r_i)=(0,0,1)` denotes ``recovered``, "
":math:`(h_i,e_i,r_i)=(0,0,0)` denotes ``susceptible``. The update of the "
"system at step :math:`k` is decomposed into three stages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIR.rst:77
#: 4cd2fb8dafe0431486764a2a5b60153d
msgid ""
"Each infected neighbor :math:`j` of node :math:`i` transmits a log-"
"probability contribution for exposure (S→E)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIR.rst:79
#: f98edbee55b84f79a03df3750b8bfabb
msgid ""
"m_{ji}^{(k)} = \\mathbf{1}\\!\\left(h_j^{(k-1)}=1 \\land "
"e_j^{(k-1)}=0\\right)\\,\\log(1-\\beta)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIR.rst:85
#: c37e5c19b880455b912b74b7b39d572e
msgid ""
"Node :math:`i` collects contributions from all neighbors :math:`N(i)` to "
"compute its exposure probability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIR.rst:87
#: a71422a61d2e43548a4e05396c9a4338
msgid "m_i^{(k)} = 1 - \\exp\\!\\left( \\sum_{j \\in N(i)} m_{ji}^{(k)} \\right)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIR.rst:92
#: 766cd81b0e1440508789f1374fab1035
msgid ""
"The indicator variables are updated with independent uniform random "
"variables :math:`U_i^{\\mathrm{exp}}, U_i^{\\mathrm{inf}}, "
"U_i^{\\mathrm{rec}} \\sim \\mathrm{Uniform}(0,1)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIR.rst:94
#: 407f3b74d803494ebef0fcb475056441
msgid ""
"\\begin{aligned}\n"
" h_i^{(k)} &=\n"
"\\begin{cases}\n"
"    1, & \\text{if } (U_i^{\\mathrm{exp}} < m_i^{(k)}) \\land "
"(h_i^{(k-1)}=0 \\land r_i^{(k-1)}=0), \\\\[4pt]\n"
"    0, & \\text{if } (U_i^{\\mathrm{rec}} < \\gamma) \\land "
"(h_i^{(k-1)}=1 \\land e_i^{(k-1)}=0), \\\\[4pt]\n"
"    h_i^{(k-1)}, & \\text{otherwise},\n"
"\\end{cases} \\\\[6pt]\n"
"e_i^{(k)} &=\n"
"\\begin{cases}\n"
"    1, & \\text{if } (U_i^{\\mathrm{exp}} < m_i^{(k)}) \\land "
"(h_i^{(k-1)}=0 \\land r_i^{(k-1)}=0), \\\\[4pt]\n"
"    0, & \\text{if } (U_i^{\\mathrm{inf}} < \\alpha) \\land e_i^{(k-1)}=1"
" , \\\\[4pt]\n"
"    e_i^{(k-1)}, & \\text{otherwise},\n"
"\\end{cases} \\\\[6pt]\n"
"r_i^{(k)} &=\n"
"\\begin{cases}\n"
"    1, & \\text{if } (U_i^{\\mathrm{rec}} < \\gamma) \\land "
"(h_i^{(k-1)}=1 \\land e_i^{(k-1)}=0), \\\\[4pt]\n"
"    r_i^{(k-1)}, & \\text{otherwise}.\n"
"\\end{cases}\n"
"\\end{aligned}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

